e linked to or differentiated from their practice elsewhere; the benefits and drawbacks of a 'nationalistic' approach to scholarship in the social sciences; the contributions of Canadian scholarship to the study of society in general and Canadian society in particular; the interaction among the social sciences in Canada and the need for inter-disciplinary studies; and the unfulfilled agenda of Canadian social science. The assessments thus delineate the peculiar problems of the social sciences in Canada as well as some of the overall problems within and among the disciplines themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aSocial sciencesvCongresses. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aCook, R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuinsberg, Tom N., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGuinsburg, T.N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, H.G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeyfitz, N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacpherson, C.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReuber, G.L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReuber, Grant, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRokeach, M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148759635440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487596354423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487596354.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aE